This paper deals with the capacity of a MIMO channel with temporal correlation, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the impact of the correlation on the capacity, which is relevant to networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of multiple antennas is a key aspect of the paper, making it relevant to the sub-category of multiple-input multiple-output (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of the results for the design of communication systems, which falls under the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
